Name: Forbidden City
Description: The Forbidden City is a palace and museum in Beijing, China. It was the former Chinese imperial palace and state residence of the Emperor of China from the Ming dynasty to the end of the Qing dynasty, between 1420 and 1924. The Forbidden City was the ceremonial and political center of the Chinese government for almost 500 years.
